    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/19.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Herrick</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>311. Auguste Peralme, naturalized as American citizen September 24, 1906,
                    impressed into Thirteenth Company of the 117th Regiment of Neims [sic] Infantry.
                    He came to this country twenty-two years ago at age of seventeen. His wife and
                    two children destitute here. Ask for release and report result.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
